.SH NAME
Element.clientTop \- Element: clientTop property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]clientTop\f[B]\f[R] read\-only property of the
\f[CR]Element\f[R] interface returns the width of the top border of an
element in pixels.
.PP
All that lies between the \f[CR]offsetTop\f[R] and \f[CR]clientTop\f[R]
is the element\(cqs border.
This is because the \f[CR]offsetTop\f[R] indicates the location of the
top of the border (not the margin) while the client area starts
immediately below the border, including padding.
Therefore, the \f[CR]clientTop\f[R] value is always equal to the
\f[CR]border\-top\-width\f[R], rounded to integer.
For example, if the computed \f[CR]border\-top\-width\f[R] is zero, then
\f[CR]clientTop\f[R] is also zero.
.SH VALUE
An integer.
.SH EXAMPLES
In the following example, the client area has a white background and a
24px black \f[CR]border\-top\f[R].
The \f[CR]clientTop\f[R] value is the distance from where the margin
(yellow) area ends and the padding and content areas (white) begin: that
is, 24px.
